snippet.textDisplay:
Bleaching your hair as a guy is so much easier (at least it was in my experience). I went in pretty much knowing what to do from watching your videos, but still felt like I didn't know anything. I only wanted highlights, by the way. I literally used a toothbrush and put bleach on my hair in stripes...I had to do about 3 rounds. The most surprising thing is that it looked amazing. Because I did multiple rounds I got different shades of blonde and I managed to make it not look patchy.
TL;DR: Fucked everything up and it still turned out great.

I bleached my hair (my stylist did), it was heavy highlighted brunette...and my curls just NEVER curled well again. I chopped off 5 inches & now I'm waiting for it to grow...so I can go curly again.
Here's the PROBLEM- As we age we get grays! And bleaching is the only way to hide it! But it kills my curls! 😭😭😭
I don't know how to win this aging game.
